DDS
Class DCPSState

java.lang.Object
  DDS.DCPSState

public final class DCPSState
extends java.lang.Object

The DCPSState class represents an enumeration of the possible states in which the publication and subscribtion infrastructure used by the DLRL can be.

Field Detail

_INITIAL

public static final int _INITIAL
This option indicates that the publication and subscribtion infrastructure is in initial mode. I.E. the application using DLRL can still insert information (in the form of registering ObjectHomes) to be used by the DLRL to derive the publication and subscribtion infrastructure from.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

INITIAL

public static final DCPSState INITIAL
A convenience wrapper for the _INITIAL option of the DCPSState enumeration.

_REGISTERED

public static final int _REGISTERED
This option indicates that the publication and subscribtion infrastructure is in registered mode. I.E. the DLRL has used the information provided by the application to derive the neccesary DCPS publication and subscribtion infrastructure. The derived entities are not yet enabled though.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

REGISTERED

public static final DCPSState REGISTERED
A convenience wrapper for the _REGISTERED option of the DCPSState enumeration.

_ENABLED

public static final int _ENABLED
This option indicates that the publication and subscribtion infrastructure is in enabled mode. I.E. the publication and subscribtion infrastructure is fully up and running and the DLRL is ready to send/receive data.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ENABLED

public static final DCPSState ENABLED
A convenience wrapper for the _ENABLED option of the DCPSState enumeration.
